Merci de diffuser largement

CALL FOR PAPERS
SPECIAL SESSION ON
“Interaction Management in Digitized Ecosystems”
SMC2021
October 17‐20, 2021 – Melbourne, Australia
http://ieeesmc2021.org/ <http://ieeesmc2021.org/>


*Session Organizer/s:*
Marie-Hélène Abel, Université de Technologie de Compiègne, France, 
marie-helene.abel@utc.fr <mailto:marie-helene.abel@utc.fr>
Giancarlo Fortino, Università di Calabria, Italy, 
giancarlo.fortino@unical.it <mailto:giancarlo.fortino@unical.it>
Álvaro Herrero, Universidad de Burgos, Spain, ahcosio@ubu.es 
<mailto:ahcosio@ubu.es>
Session area: Human‐Machine Systems
Technical Committee name: French Chapter 28

*Session Description:*
In the era of Information and Communication Technology, everybody is 
connected and asked to manage
interactions among people, between people and artificial systems, and 
among systems themselves in a single
digital ecosystem. This special session takes place in the 4.0 world and 
deals with the problems related to the
use of different devices, applications or documents. In this world, we 
need to share and exchange data,
information, and services, which leads to many different problems, 
namely interoperability, trust, privacy,
identity, acquaintances, accessibility, usability or ethics.
The goal of the Special Session is to provide a forum for researchers 
and practitioners involved in different
and complementary domains to confront research results and to discuss 
key problems.


*The major topics of interest of this special session include, but are 
not limited to:*
 Numerical Identity, Trust and Privacy
 Knowledge Engineering and Management
 Cooperation and Organization
 Interactions in Cyber Physical Systems
 System of Systems
 Recommender System/Context‐Aware Recommender System
 Human Machine Interaction (assistance or representation)
 IoT and Data/Information Management
 Ethical approaches to Data Privacy Protection

Applications in several domains like Health, Crisis Management, 
Manufacturing, Smart Mobility, Smart cities or Training are welcome.

This special session is a result of a joint effort by the French, 
Italian and Spanish SMC Chapters.

*Keywords: * Computational Collective Intelligence, Cybernetics for 
Cyber‐Physical Systems, Expert and Knowledge‐Based Systems, Industry 
4.0, Industry 5.0, Multi‐Agent Systems, Human‐Machine Cooperation, IoT

*SUBMISSION*
Papers must be submitted electronically for peer review through 
PaperCept by April 5, 2021:
https://conf.papercept.net/conferences/scripts/start.pl 
<https://conf.papercept.net/conferences/scripts/start.pl>. In PaperCept, 
click on the SMC 2021 link
“Submit a contribution to SMC 2021” and follow the steps. The code of 
the special session is: 553ta
All papers must be written in English and should describe original work. 
For guidelines, please follow the SMC
website link http://ieeesmc2021.org/call‐for‐papers/ 
<http://ieeesmc2021.org/call%E2%80%90for%E2%80%90papers/>

*DEADLINES*
April 5, 2021: deadline for paper submission
May 26, 2021: notification of paper acceptance/rejection
July 12, 2021: deadline for final camera‐ready papers.
-- 

Mickael Coustaty
Maître de Conférence / Associate Professor
Co-directeur du Master Tiers de Confiance et Sécurité Numérique
Directeur du laboratoire commun IDEAS
LABORATOIRE L3i
